title: I Am Sam
overview: A mentally handicapped man fights for custody of his 7-year-old daughter and in the process teaches his cold-hearted lawyer the value of love and family.

title: My Name Is Khan
overview: An Indian Muslim man with Asperger's syndrome takes a challenge to speak to the President of the United States seriously and embarks on a cross-country journey.

title: Udaan
overview: Expelled from his school, a 16-year old boy returns home to his abusive and oppressive father.

title: Roma
overview: A year in the life of a middle-class family's maid in Mexico City in the early 1970s.
stars: ['Yalitza Aparicio', 'Marina de Tavira', 'Diego Cortina Autrey', 'Carlos Peralta']

title: Fight Club
overview: An insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soapmaker form an underground fight club that evolves into something much, much more.

title: Gegen die Wand
overview: With the intention to break free from the strict familial restrictions, a suicidal young woman sets up a marriage of convenience with a forty-year-old addict, an act that will lead to an outburst of envious love.

title: Magnolia
overview: An epic mosaic of interrelated characters in search of love, forgiveness, and meaning in the San Fernando Valley.

title: Short Term 12
overview: A 20-something supervising staff member of a residential treatment facility navigates the troubled waters of that world alongside her co-worker and longtime boyfriend.

title: The Florida Project
overview: Set over one summer, the film follows precocious six-year-old Moonee as she courts mischief and adventure with her ragtag playmates and bonds with her rebellious but caring mother, all while living in the shadows of Walt Disney World.

title: Capharnaüm
overview: While serving a five-year sentence for a violent crime, a 12-year-old boy sues his parents for neglect.
stars: ['Zain Al Rafeea', 'Yordanos Shiferaw', 'Boluwatife Treasure Bankole', 'Kawsar Al Haddad']

title: Babam ve Oglum
overview: The family of a left-wing journalist is torn apart after the military coup of Turkey in 1980.

title: Titanic
overview: A seventeen-year-old aristocrat falls in love with a kind but poor artist aboard the luxurious, ill-fated R.M.S. Titanic.

title: Platoon
overview: Chris Taylor, a neophyte recruit in Vietnam, finds himself caught in a battle of wills between two sergeants, one good and the other evil. A shrewd examination of the brutality of war and the duality of man in conflict.

title: Wonder
overview: Based on the New York Times bestseller, this movie tells the incredibly inspiring and heartwarming story of August Pullman, a boy with facial differences who enters the fifth grade, attending a mainstream elementary school for the first time.

title: Boyhood
overview: The life of Mason, from early childhood to his arrival at college.

title: Viskningar och rop
overview: When a woman dying of cancer in early twentieth-century Sweden is visited by her two sisters, long-repressed feelings between the siblings rise to the surface.

title: Miracle in cell NO.7
overview: A story of love between a mentally-ill father who was wrongly accused of murder and his lovely six years old daughter. The prison would be their home. Based on the 2013 Korean movie 7-beon-bang-ui seon-mul (2013).
stars: ['Aras Bulut Iynemli', 'Nisa Sofiya Aksongur', 'Deniz Baysal', 'Celile Toyon Uysal']

title: Vozvrashchenie
overview: In the Russian wilderness, two brothers face a range of new, conflicting emotions when their father - a man they know only through a single photograph - resurfaces.

title: Taare Zameen Par
overview: An eight-year-old boy is thought to be a lazy trouble-maker, until the new art teacher has the patience and compassion to discover the real problem behind his struggles in school.

title: Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?
overview: A bitter, aging couple, with the help of alcohol, use their young houseguests to fuel anguish and emotional pain towards each other over the course of a distressing night.
